            <title>[FLINK-18880] Respect configurations defined in flink-conf.yaml and environment variables when executing in local mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-18880</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the configurations defined in flink-conf.yaml and environment variables are not respected when PyFlink jobs are executed in local mode. It will cause a few problems, including but not limited to the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Users could not configure the heap memory used by the gateway server. It may cause OOM issues in scenarios such as Table.to_pandas when the content of the Table is big.&#160;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There is no easy way for users to specify hadoop classpath&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
